32100.m_mIntroduce:
"The last remnants of Piera's will as she merges with the Spirit Bone Tower.
The girl learned forbidden arts, stole the salt coffin, and sailed across the sea to Sunset Isle all for this very moment. For the sake of her clan and those standing before her, she persists onward, despite the prospects of death."

32200.m_mIntroduce: "One of many Spirit Bone Towers preserved in a salt coffin that are indestructible due to a fusion of blood and bones from the Paracelsus family. Like a massive piece of amber, the salt coffin perfectly preserves the remains within, seemingly rendering null the passage of time."

32201.m_mIntroduce: "Perhaps the most distinctive Spirit Bone Tower, it was clearly a prized piece of work. The tower is meticulously constructed from the skulls of the Paracelsus family, and silently displays the obsessive nature of its creators."

32410.m_mIntroduce: "With the fall of the former ruler Zagon, a vicious rat-like Blood Beast swiftly seized power, becoming the new sovereign of Starfall Valley. Though it still bears traces of Zagon, years of mineral corrosion have eroded all remnants of its former grandeur."

32500.m_mIntroduce: "A Sapphire Isle Sage, responsible for maintaining order at the auction house and throughout the bay. Known as the keeper of order, he bears an uncanny resemblance to Captain Goldland."

33103.m_mIntroduce: "A mysterious figure who attacked Agares in the Main Hall of the Tempus Church."

33180.m_mIntroduce: "A Bloodborn girl who suddenly emerged from the shadowy caverns, fangs gleaming coldly in the darkness, eyes glowing with dangerous crimson. Strangely, she now carefully shields a frail human boy behind her."

33190.m_mIntroduce: "The Mouret boy cowering behind the Bloodborn girl, clutching tightly to a flower basket fragrant with herbs. He stares at Agnes like a frightened animal, his pants stained with mud, his young face a mixture of fear and defiance."

33191.m_mIntroduce: "The Mouret boy cowering behind the Bloodborn girl, clutching tightly to a flower basket fragrant with herbs. He stares at Agnes like a frightened animal, his pants stained with mud, his young face a mixture of fear and defiance."

33200.m_mIntroduce: "A schemer cloaked in a commander's mantle, twisting his kin into instruments of war with plague. With a cold smile, he cleanses the blood upon his late sister's relic, murmuring: 'The worth of death lies in stoking the fires of hatred.' This serpent of Ganelon shall one day devour his own homeland."

33210.m_mIntroduce: "When stone wings shielded the girl one final time, shackles dissolved into drifting petals. Even as his spirit faded, his purpose endured—he fought, he stood firm, he protected. He is Michelangelo."

33220.m_mIntroduce: "A spirit reborn as an exquisite doll, her innocence steeped in blood. Beneath her mantle, hundreds of hands writhe in secret—her collection curated to preserve 'family harmony.' She is the queen of puppets, Sirene."

33230.m_mIntroduce: "A peasant residing in Mouret. Invaders turned him into a raging monster, and the blood-covered scythe in hand is a testament to his brutality."

33231.m_mIntroduce: "A peasant residing in Mouret. Invaders turned him into a raging monster, and the blood-covered scythe in hand is a testament to his brutality."

33232.m_mIntroduce: "A Mouret villager who takes shifts with James tending to the afflicted in the cave. He appears dutiful on the outside, yet secretly harbors thoughts of betrayal toward his kin."

33240.m_mIntroduce: "A hunter residing in Mouret. Their archery skills retain deadly precision against the invaders."

33241.m_mIntroduce: "A hunter residing in Mouret. Their archery skills retain deadly precision against the invaders."

33250.m_mIntroduce: "A farmer from Mouret, who even without any proper weapon, still grips a pitchfork with unwavering resolve, sworn to defend this land until the final breath."

33260.m_mIntroduce: "A shadow crouched in the cave's depths, using twisted claws to dig out underground springs. After pushing the last half-bowl of water to a child, it sank completely into the abyss."

33261.m_mIntroduce: "A shadow crouched in the cave's depths, using twisted claws to dig out underground springs. After pushing the last half-bowl of water to a child, it sank completely into the abyss."

33270.m_mIntroduce: "Their claws rake against the stone walls, the protective amulet from home hanging around the neck. Festering flesh weeps Black Blood, and in the eyes lingers a desperate glimmer of pleading."

33271.m_mIntroduce: "Their claws rake against the stone walls, the protective amulet from home hanging around the neck. Festering flesh weeps Black Blood, and in the eyes lingers a desperate glimmer of pleading."

33280.m_mIntroduce: "The Full Moon burns the Black Blood within their bodies, muscles swelling like lava bursting from rock. They bite at their own flesh, seeking only to end the agony of being consumed by Black Blood."

33290.m_mIntroduce: "Ganelon soldiers never question right from wrong, but simply obey orders out of habit. It is this blind compliance that makes them part of evil's plan."

33292.m_mIntroduce: "Ganelon soldiers never question right from wrong, but simply obey orders out of habit. It is this blind compliance that makes them part of evil's plan."

33300.m_mIntroduce: "Most Ganelon soldiers come from humble families and possess unwavering loyalty to their commander. This blind trust makes them fearless on the battlefield, charging without hesitation even when facing the most formidable enemies."

40010.m_mIntroduce: "The head chef of the "El Dorado," responsible for meal preparations. Proficient with a pair of meat cleavers, he serves up a course of combat expertise."

40011.m_mIntroduce: "The second mate of the "El Dorado," familiar with the art of combat at sea. <color=#D63536>He capitalizes on the ship's sway to nimbly evade incoming attacks</color>."

40012.m_mIntroduce: "A sailor working aboard the "El Dorado." Greedy and aggressive, they are fond of gambling and liquor and adept at fighting with hatchets."

42010.m_mIntroduce:
"A Baphomet member who ascended to elder in his youth. The purple Soul Pyre and blade he wields manifest his boundless ambition.
He will prove he is no lackey, no brute, no inferior—the throne of the Lord of the Bloodborn shall be his."

42011.m_mIntroduce:

50010.m_mIntroduce: "The gate to the Ashen Garden, the forbidden grounds of the Ganelon family."

50020.m_mIntroduce: "Erupting Fungi are active and explode upon contact, dealing AoE DMG while also detonating other Erupting Fungi in range."

50120.m_mIntroduce: "Cannons installed on the deck of the El Dorado by Goldland. After all, smuggling Blood Beasts is a dangerous, albeit lucrative business."

50150.m_mIntroduce:
"An ancient, nameless statue stands alone on Sunset Isle.

Time and sea winds have claimed all who remembered its purpose."

50160.m_mIntroduce: "On the barren isle, waves crash in endless rhythm, like a lullaby sung to an empty cradle."

90101.m_mName: "William Goldland, Captain of the El Dorado."
90101.m_mIntroduce: "When his crimes can no longer be concealed, the Black Blood merchant sheds all pretense. He will prove to the world that he is no mere shadow of Goldland — but the true master of the El Dorado. And his name is William Goldland."

90102.m_mIntroduce: "The Black Blood has transformed William into a beast driven purely by desire. Timidity and self-doubt are stripped away. Ranna is beckoning to him — and there, where the claws of fear can never reach, lies only the promise of eternal peace."

90103.m_mIntroduce: "The Black Blood has transformed William into a beast driven purely by desire. Timidity and self-doubt are stripped away. Ranna is beckoning to him — and there, where the claws of fear can never reach, lies only the promise of eternal peace."

90105.m_mIntroduce: "A sailor fully mutated by Black Blood. The infectious Calamity "Famine" has rendered it a living embodiment of "devourance," its monstrous maw serving as a testament to this concept."

90703.m_mIntroduce:
"A crab that escaped the El Dorado, once a Black Blood experiement subject.
Its shell bears the mark of a sea beast and the number zero. Only the bottle it clutches offers solace from its former torment."
